---
// What You'll Learn - Our Methods Style (Wix inspired)
---

<section id="kids" class="py-24 bg-white">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
    <!-- Section Header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-16 fade-up">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900">
        What You'll Learn
      </h2>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Images Wrapper - for positioning orange rectangle -->
  <div class="learn-images-wrapper">
    <!-- Orange rectangle behind images -->
    <div class="orange-rectangle"></div>
    <!-- Images Container - outside container to allow full viewport width -->
    <div class="learn-images-container">
      <div class="learn-images-grid">
      <!-- Image5: Escape technique demo -->
      <div class="fade-up learn-image-item">
        <div class="learn-image learn-image-5">
          <div class="w-full h-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-sm">
            [Image5: Escape technique demo]
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="learn-text-content">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
            Escape Techniques
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Learn how to get out of holds, grabs, and uncomfortable situations. Because "freeze
            and hope for the best" is not a strategy we endorse.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Image6: Ground fighting position -->
      <div class="fade-up learn-image-item">
        <div class="learn-image learn-image-6">
          <div class="w-full h-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-sm">
            [Image6: Ground fighting position]
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="learn-text-content">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
            Ground Defense
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Most real fights end up on the ground. We'll teach you how to defend yourself from the
            worst positions, not just the pretty ones that look good in movies.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Image7: Submission hold -->
      <div class="fade-up learn-image-item">
        <div class="learn-image learn-image-7">
          <div class="w-full h-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-sm">
            [Image7: Submission hold]
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="learn-text-content">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
            Control Techniques
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Master chokes and joint locks that leverage technique over strength. You don't need
            muscles when you have physics and the element of surprise.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Image8: Striking practice -->
      <div class="fade-up learn-image-item">
        <div class="learn-image learn-image-8">
          <div class="w-full h-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-sm">
            [Image8: Striking practice]
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="learn-text-content">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
            Striking Basics
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Sometimes you need to throw hands. We'll teach you how to punch, elbow, and kick
            effectively - not the limp-wristed slaps you see in bad action movies.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  /* Wrapper for positioning orange rectangle */
  #kids .learn-images-wrapper {
    position: relative;
    margin-top: 185px; /* Vertical spacing: 90px (same as gallery) + 95px (orange rectangle offset) = 185px total */
  }

  /* Images container - handles overflow */
  #kids .learn-images-container {
    overflow-x: hidden; /* Prevent horizontal scroll */
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1; /* Above orange rectangle */
  }

  /* Images grid - flexbox layout with 20px gaps, 80px margins */
  #kids .learn-images-grid {
    display: flex;
    gap: 20px;
    margin-left: 80px; /* 80px from left viewport edge */
    margin-right: 80px; /* 80px from right viewport edge */
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1; /* Above orange rectangle */
  }

  /* Each image item - flex column to stack image and text */
  #kids .learn-image-item {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
  }

  /* Image styling - width = 90% of height (so height = width / 0.9) */
  #kids .learn-image {
    background-color: #1f2937; /* bg-gray-800 */
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: 0 10px 15px -3px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1), 0 4px 6px -2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05); /* shadow-lg */
    border-radius: 0; /* No rounded corners */
    /* Width: (viewport - 160px margins - 60px gaps) / 4 */
    width: calc((100vw - 220px) / 4);
    /* Height: width / 0.9 (since width = 90% of height) */
    height: calc(((100vw - 220px) / 4) / 0.9);
  }

  /* Text content below each image - centered and same width as image */
  #kids .learn-text-content {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 1.5rem; /* Space between image and text */
    width: calc((100vw - 220px) / 4); /* Same width as image */
    padding-left: 40px;
    padding-right: 40px;
  }

  /* Orange rectangle: behind images, left edge touches viewport, 80% width, 95px above images, 320px height */
  #kids .orange-rectangle {
    position: absolute;
    /* Position: 95px above the learn-images-grid */
    top: -95px;
    /* Left edge: touching left viewport edge */
    left: 0;
    /* Width: 80% of viewport */
    width: 80vw;
    /* Height: fixed 320px */
    height: 320px;
    background-color: #f97316; /* Orange color */
    border-radius: 0; /* No rounded corners */
    z-index: 0; /* Behind images */
  }
</style>
